        "body": "Soon may the last glad song arise\n<br>Through all the millions of the skies;\n<br>That song of triumph which records\n<br>That all the earth is now the Lord's.\n<br>\n<br>Let thrones and powers and kingdoms be\n<br>Obedient, mighty God, to Thee;\n<br>And over land and stream and main\n<br>Wave Thou the scepter of Thy reign.\n<br>\n<br>O let the anthem now might swell,\n<br>And host to host the triumph tell,\n<br>Till not one rebel heart remains,\n<br>But over all the Savior reigns!"
